HEADWORD: Semicrystalline
<hw>Sem`i*crys"tal*line</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Half crystalline; -- said of certain eruptive
rocks composed partly of crystalline, partly of amorphous
matter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

